text: Swofford is an unincorporated community in Lewis County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Swofford was established in 1890, and remained in operation until 1922. The community was named after T. F. Swofford, who was credited with securing a post office for the town. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Lewis County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Swofford, Washington
